# 1. General Provisions

1.1. Participants in the professional eSports competition "Esports League Super Cup" (hereinafter referred to as the Competition) must be familiar with and comply with the Competition Regulations.

1.1.1. Competition Regulations are the Technical Rules, the Regulations of the professional eSports competition "Esports League Super Cup", as well as other documents, the list of which is determined by the Competition Regulations.

1.1.2. Submitting an application to participate in the Competition confirms that each participant has read the provisions of the regulatory documents and agreed to comply with them.

# 2. Game Settings 

2.1. Game Servers are provided by FACEIT with such regions: Moscow, Netherlands, UK, Germany, Sweden, France, Finland.

2.2. Game Servers settings:

| Command  | Description |
| ------------- | ------------- |
| 'mp_maxrounds 24'  | Rounds |
| 'mp_roundtime 1.92'  | Round Duration  |
| 'mp_startmoney 800'  | Start Money  |
| 'mp_maxmoney 16000'  | Max money  |
| 'mp_freezetime 20'  | Time to start a round  |
| 'mp_c4timer 40'  | Bomb duration  |
| 'mp_buytime 20'  | Time to buy from the start of the round  |

2.3 All matches of the Competition will take place exclusively on servers created on the tournament platform approved by the Organiser.

2.4. You can request a server change, but only if all match participants are experiencing connection issues with the server.

2.5. The server may be replaced by the REF decision.

2.6. To submit a server change request, the player experiencing the issue must create a request via **CALL ADMIN** button in FACEIT match room and provide evidence. Requests submitted elsewhere or without evidence will be rejected. If the evidence provided indicates server issues, a new server will be assigned. The connection IP will be changed on the match page. If the evidence is insufficient, the referee reserves the right to reject the request.

2.7. If a round is interrupted for technical reasons, the round must be replayed using the “backup” function.

2.8. If damage was dealt in the round, no “backup” is made.

2.9. If all players get disconnected from the server and cannot connect via “backup”, a replay on another server is conducted.


# 3. Check-in

3.1. After registration is complete, the team captain must confirm participation in the Competition on his page by clicking on the corresponding “Confirm” button, within the time period specified in schedule.

3.2. Confirmation of participation in the Competition at a time not specified in its schedule is impossible.

3.3. Once confirmation of participation in the Competition is complete, a tournament bracket is formed and published in the "bracket" section on the Competition page.


# 4. Veto Process 

4.1. Map veto order:
Team A is a team that starts the veto process
Team B is a second team that continues the veto process

4.1.1 For BO3 Matches

| Team A remove a map |
| Team B remove a map |
| Team A picks 1st Map of the match |
| Team B picks 2nd Map of the match |
| Team A remove a map |
| Team B remove a map |
| The leftover map is left for a decider (if needed) |

4.1.2. For BO1 Matches

| Team A remove a map |
| Team B remove a map |
| Team A remove a map |
| Team B remove a map |
| Team A remove a map |
| Team B remove a map |
| The leftover map is left for a decider |


4.2. Which team is Team A and which team is Team B will be randomly chosen by FACEIT 

# 5. Pauses 

5.1. In case of a situation when one or more players from the team get disconnected, a pause of no more than 10 minutes is set. In case one or more players are unable to continue the game for reasons independent of them, the decision on the result of the match or replay is made by the tournament referee.

5.2. Each team has the right to take a pause during the match, with the captain indicating the reason for the pause in the chat (tactical, technical). The total time of tactical pauses must not exceed 4 minutes per match (2 minutes per team). The duration of one tactical pause is 30 seconds.

5.3. Tech Pause can be used by typing !tech or !pause in game chat (ALL chat)

5.4. Tactical Pause can be used by typing !tac or using in game voting (ESC - Call Vote - Call A Tactical Timeout)

5.5. Players may pause the game only for the reasons stated below and must immediately inform their opponents and the referees of the reason for the pause. Acceptable reasons include the following:

- Unintentional disconnection

-Equipment malfunction or software problems (e.g. monitor power problems, peripheral device failure or game crash).

5.6. Matches will not be stopped and/or rounds will not be restored or replayed in cases where the incident is due to the obvious fault of the participant (e.g. incorrect weapon purchase).

5.7. The pause function can be used at any time, but will only take effect during the 20 second countdown to the start of the main round time. If the pause is taken during the 20 second countdown to the start of the round, it will be applied immediately. Otherwise, the pause will take effect during the next 20 second countdown to the start of the round.

5.8. The competition administration may pause the game on its part, or ask the participants to do so when necessary.



